cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the identification of smartphone users based on their usage patterns, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also uses data from the StudentLife dataset, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the impact of mood on biometric systems, which could be considered a topic in computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper analyzes smartphone usage patterns, which could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
